<treatmentCitationGroup id="AB0C0C38FFC3FF926BB0FA59FCA0FA63" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">
<treatmentCitation id="0ABD0D07FFC3FF926BB0FA59FD6BFA04" author="Forel, A." box="[151,693,1430,1452]" page="332" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" year="1911">
<taxonomicName id="4C1C5095FFC3FF926BB0FA59FD6BFA04" authority="Forel, 1911: 332" authorityName="Forel" authorityPageNumber="332" authorityYear="1911" box="[151,693,1430,1452]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="caespitum" variety="chefketi">
<emphasis id="B968F704FFC3FF926BB0FA59FE56FA04" box="[151,392,1431,1452]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">Tetramorium caespitum</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B968F704FFC3FF926A9CFA58FDD4FA04" box="[443,522,1430,1452]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">chefketi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFC3FF926937FA58FD6BFA04" author="Forel, A." box="[528,693,1430,1452]" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" pagination="331 - 400" refId="ref7217" refString="Forel, A. (1911) Fourmis nouvelles ou interessantes. Bulletin de la Societ Vaudoise des Sciences Naturelles, 47, 331 - 400." type="journal article" year="1911">Forel, 1911:332</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</treatmentCitation>
. Raised to species: 
<treatmentCitation id="0ABD0D07FFC3FF92685BFA58FB11FA04" author="Agosti, D. &amp; Collingwood, C. A." box="[892,1231,1430,1452]" page="56" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" year="1987">
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFC3FF92685BFA58FB11FA04" author="Agosti, D. &amp; Collingwood, C. A." box="[892,1231,1430,1452]" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" pagination="51 - 62" refId="ref5886" refString="Agosti, D. &amp; Collingwood, C. A. (1987) A provisional list of the Balkan ants (Hym. Formicidae) and a key to the worker caste. I. Synonymic list. Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 60, 51 - 62." type="journal article" year="1987">Agosti &amp; Collingwood, 1987: 56</bibRefCitation>
</treatmentCitation>
. Senior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C5095FFC3FF926BE0FA78FCA4FA63" authority=": Csosz, Radchenko &amp; Schulz, 2007: 18" authorityName="Csosz, Radchenko &amp; Schulz" authorityPageNumber="18" authorityYear="2007" box="[199,890,1461,1483]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="turcomanicum">
<emphasis id="B968F704FFC3FF926BE0FA78FE3AFA63" box="[199,484,1462,1483]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">Tetramorium turcomanicum</emphasis>
: 
<treatmentCitation id="0ABD0D07FFC3FF926AD6FA7BFCA4FA63" author="Csosz, S. &amp; Radchenko, A. &amp; Schulz, A." box="[497,890,1461,1483]" page="18" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" year="2007">
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFC3FF926AD6FA7BFCA4FA63" author="Csosz, S. &amp; Radchenko, A. &amp; Schulz, A." box="[497,890,1461,1483]" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" pagination="1 - 38" refId="ref6921" refString="Csosz, S., Radchenko, A. &amp; Schulz, A. (2007) Taxonomic revision of the Palaearctic Tetramorium chefketi species complex (Hymenoptera: Formicidae). Zootaxa, 1405, 1 - 38." type="journal article" year="2007">Csõsz, Radchenko &amp; Schulz, 2007: 18</bibRefCitation>
</treatmentCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C306789DFFC3FF926BB0FA39FCC0F940" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA32B16FFC3FF926BB0FA39FCC0F940" blockId="9.[151,1437,1527,1768]" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">
This species was recorded from 
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFC3FF92692FFA39FD42F9B8" box="[520,668,1527,1552]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFC3FF92698BFA39FC55F9B8" author="Collingwood, C. A." box="[684,907,1527,1552]" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" pagination="230 - 302" refId="ref6815" refString="Collingwood, C. A. (1985) Hymenoptera: Fam. Formicidae of Saudi Arabia. Fauna Saudi Arabia, 7, 230 - 302." type="journal article" year="1985">Collingwood, 1985</bibRefCitation>
), 
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFC3FF926886FA39FC3BF9B8" box="[929,997,1527,1552]" name="Oman" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">Oman</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFC3FF926F38FA36FBB3F9A7" box="[1055,1133,1528,1551]" name="Yemen" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">Yemen</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFC3FF926F5AFA39FF0DF99D" author="Collingwood, C. A. &amp; Agosti, D." pageId="9" pageNumber="574" pagination="300 - 385" refId="ref6843" refString="Collingwood, C. A. &amp; Agosti, D. (1996) Formicidae of Saudi Arabia (Part 2). Fauna of Saudi Arabia, 15, 300 - 385." type="journal article" year="1996">Collingwood and Agosti, 1996</bibRefCitation>
). Outside Arabia, it has been reported from several parts of the Palaearctic region including southern Europe (
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFC3FF926BB9F9F1FF2CF9F0" box="[158,242,1599,1624]" name="Greece" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">Greece</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFC3FF926A25F9F1FEB8F9F0" box="[258,358,1599,1624]" name="Bulgaria" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">Bulgaria</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFC3FF926A51F9F1FE2BF9F0" box="[374,501,1599,1624]" name="Macedonia" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">Macedonia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFC3FF926922F9F1FDB1F9F0" box="[517,623,1599,1624]" name="Romania" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">Romania</collectingCountry>
), southern 
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFC3FF9269D4F9F1FC8EF9F0" box="[755,848,1599,1624]" name="Ukraine" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
, south of western 
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFC3FF926F08F9F1FBA2F9F0" box="[1071,1148,1599,1624]" name="Russia" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">Russia</collectingCountry>
, northwestern Caucasus, 
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFC3FF926BB0F9AAFF36F9D5" box="[151,232,1636,1661]" name="Turkey" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">Turkey</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFC3FF926BD3F9AAFE4CF9D5" box="[244,402,1636,1661]" name="Turkmenistan" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">Turkmenistan</collectingCountry>
, northern 
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFC3FF926921F9AAFD52F9D5" box="[518,652,1636,1661]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
, southeastern Siberia, to the east to 
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFC3FF926F0EF9AAFB74F9D4" box="[1065,1194,1636,1660]" name="Kyrgyzstan" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">Kyrgyzstan</collectingCountry>
and Altai Mountains (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFC3FF926BB9F949FEA9F908" author="Csosz, S. &amp; Radchenko, A. &amp; Schulz, A." box="[158,375,1671,1696]" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" pagination="1 - 38" refId="ref6921" refString="Csosz, S., Radchenko, A. &amp; Schulz, A. (2007) Taxonomic revision of the Palaearctic Tetramorium chefketi species complex (Hymenoptera: Formicidae). Zootaxa, 1405, 1 - 38." type="journal article" year="2007">
Csõsz 
<emphasis id="B968F704FFC3FF926BCAF947FEF7F908" box="[237,297,1671,1696]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">et al.</emphasis>
, 2007
</bibRefCitation>
). At Rawdhat Khorim this species is relatively common and observed foraging on 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C5095FFC3FF926E1AF949FEFEF96D" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rhamnaceae" genus="Ziziphus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nummularia">
<emphasis id="B968F704FFC3FF926E1AF949FEFEF96D" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">Ziziphus nummularia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Burm. f) Wight &amp; Arn. (
<taxonomicName id="4C1C5095FFC3FF926967F962FD08F96D" box="[576,726,1708,1733]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rhamnaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Rhamnaceae</taxonomicName>
). The species has two abundance peaks, in June and November. It was collected using pitfall traps and beating vegetation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
